name: Push-ups
description: 50 to 100 push-ups should be enough to maintain a good upper body.

name: Plank up-downs
description: Add 2 or 3 sets of 15 to 20 repetitions of the up down plank to your full body workouts.

name: Split lunge jumps
description: Beginners should aim for 5 to 10 reps on each leg or 30 seconds total.

name: Sit up
description: The American College of Sports Medicine recommends three sets of 8 to 12 repetitions three times per week.

name: Tai Chi
description: We recommend practicing a little bit every day, at least 10 minutes.

name: Hip thrust
description: Try three 30-second sets of hip thrusts at the start of the day to get those muscles firing.

name: High Jumps
description: The weekly jumping sessions should be much shorter (6-8 jumps) and the intensity levels very high.
